Short answer — documented behavior:

- rlm_context_query can return an empty result set: the context-query implementation builds a response containing "sections" (the selected sections). If nothing is selected, "sections" will be empty and total_tokens will be 0 (truncated will be false, session_context may be null). (See "Context Query Implementation" code sample.)

- Some endpoints/clients use a 404-style error when no context is available. The docs include a 404 example JSON:
  {
    "error": { "code": "NOT_FOUND", "message": "Context not found" }
  }
  (See "404 Not Found" snippet.)

- UX guidance: show a helpful empty state when there is no data (helpful message, padding, and action buttons / CTAs to index docs). The docs also advise indexing your docs (via the dashboard) so queries return useful context. (See "4. Empty States" and "Your First Query" notes.)

These points are taken directly from the provided documentation.
